The treatment of gender roles is deeply baseless and ultimately absurd—no human attribute or capability is intrinsically tied to so-called ""feminine"" or ""masculine"" categories. These labels are social constructs that exist only in the minds of people who insist on such nonsense, zealously defending cultural mythologies while pasting psychological depth and magnetism onto outdated hierarchies that invariably diminish value and potential. By pretending certain behaviors or abilities ""belong"" to one ""gender"" over another, society has created an educational system that groom people toward artificial identity conformities rather than worthwhile self-exploration. This artificially-educated paradigm causes so many human spirits to remain closed-circuit, short-circuiting personal growth before minds can least civilize their inner landscapes. When you treat people as embodiments of fabricated gendered stereotypes rather than as individual human experiences and perspectives, you deny them the chance to become fully themselves, constrained instead by embarrassing social norms that expect nothing at all from them. The real betrayal isn't challenging these absurd constructs—it's pretending they act as guidance rather than injunctions to actively destroy individual identities.
